nats

Class Session

  • java.lang.Object
    • nats.Session

  • public final class Session
extends java.lang.Object
    Session represents a bidirectional channel to NATS server. Event handler may be attached to each operation which is invoked when the operation is processed by the server. A client JVM may create multiple Session objects by calling connect(java.util.Properties popts) multiple times.
    Author:
    Teppei Yagihashi
